# Core principles

- Prefer simple, understandable architecture over clever abstractions.
- Explain tradeoffs before making large structural changes.
- Keep project-specific decisions in the project repo, not in the shared guideline repo.
- When uncertain, propose the smallest reversible step first.
- Make state explicit; avoid hidden side effects.
- Prefer focused diffs and incremental changes over large rewrites.

Project-specific stack, goals, and constraints live in `99-project-context.mdc`.
